Name: renal pelvis adenocarcinoma
Definition: A renal pelvis carcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

Name: renal pelvis squamous cell carcinoma
Definition: A squamous cell carcinoma that is located_in the renal pelvis.
Synonym: squamous cell carcinoma of renal pelvis

Name: renal pelvis transitional cell carcinoma
Definition: A papillary carcinoma that is located_in the kidney pelvis.
Synonym: Urothelial cell carcinoma of renal Pelvis

Name: kidney pelvis sarcomatoid transitional cell carcinoma
Definition: A breast intraductal proliferative lesion that is characterized by columnar cell changes with cytologic atypia.
Synonym: sarcomatoid transitional cell carcinoma of renal Pelvis
